Unilever Is Interested in Acquisitions in Germany, FTD Reports

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-08-23T02:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/unilever-is-interested-in-acquisitions-in-germany-ftd-reports.html
Unilever, the world’s second-largest
consumer-goods company, is open for an acquisition of a national
brand in  Germany  as consolidation in the industry continues,
 Financial Times Deutschland  reported today, citing an interview
with Harry Brouwer, the head of Unilever’s German operations.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  